T4	p 207 1055	 (ANSA) - BARI, OCTOBER 06 - Xylella is still advancing towards the province of Bari and infects another 42 olive trees: this was detected by Coldiretti Puglia on the basis of the tenth monitoring with laboratory analyzes which confirmed the disease on 9 olive trees in Fasano, 14 in Martina Franca and 2 in Locorotondo, all in the containment area, while there are 17 olive trees infected by Xylella in Polignano, of which 11 in the buffer zone and 6 in the free zone."To try to reverse the trend - they say from the organization - Coldiretti and Unaprol are engaged in an attempt to save the plain of monumental olive trees from the Xylella bacterium which is destroying Apulian olive growing, with grafts and supporting new surveillance methods, such as the canine task force, with the support of the researchers of the Ipsp of the Cnr". (ANSA).
